## 2026-02-22 â€” Mandatory checks after every code change

### What changed
- After **every** code change, run:
  1. `npx eslint --fix <changed files>` â€” auto-fix and lint check
  2. `npm run check` â€” TypeScript + svelte-check

### Commands

```bash
npx eslint --fix src/path/to/file.svelte src/path/to/other.ts
npm run check
```

### Why
- The project uses strict ESLint with many rules (imports, prettier, unicorn, sonarjs)
- `svelte-check` catches type errors in `.svelte` files that `tsc` cannot see
- Without this, formatting and type errors accumulate silently

